    public abstract class ExprConstant

    A constant-valued expression. This class only serves to hold static methods for creating constants.

      • createConstant

        public static Expression createConstant(FENode context,
                                        java.lang.String val)
        Create a new constant-valued expression corresponding to a String value. val must be a valid real number, according to java.lang.Double.valueOf(), excepting that it may end in "i" to indicate an imaginary value. This attempts to create an integer if possible, and a real-valued expression if possible; however, it may also create an ExprComplex with a zero (null) real part. Eexpressions like "3+4i" need to be parsed into separate expressions.
        Parameters:
        context - file and line number for the string
        val - string containing the constant to create
        Returns:
        an expression corresponding to the string value
